<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em>Book title</em> Year of publication, Publisher, Place of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Book title">Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</span></em>
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">1981</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Secretariat of the World Meteorological Organization</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Geneva</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
For a numbered edition, place the abbreviation, for a work that has no author, after the publication year. 
This part should not be italicised. Use rev. edn, for revised editions.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Book title">Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</span></em>
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">1981</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="edition">2nd edn</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Secretariat of the World Meteorological Organization</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Geneva</span>.
</blockquote>
