<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
If you are citing a work which has no author, the first few words of the title should be used. 
The title of the book is italicised.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	<em>Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</em> (1981) provides&hellip;
	<br>
	or
	<br>
	This can be shown by&hellip;(<em>Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</em> 1981).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation fewer than 30 words, use single quotation marks and include page
numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The <em>Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</em> (1981, p. 56) states that &#8216;chocolate 
	has several health benefits&#8217;.
	<br>
	Alternatively: Therefore, &#8216;chocolate has several health benefits&#8217; 
	(<em>Guide to agricultural meteorological practices</em> 1981, p. 56).
</blockquote>
